---

<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-recon-definition">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In plain terms</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Reconciliation, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-recon-accounts" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What gets reconciled</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every account that should agree with something external.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Skipping any of these is how books pass a glance and fail a real review.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for d in deliverables %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ d.num }}</span><h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ d.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-recon-signals">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">When real reconciliation earns its keep</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is yes.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Most owners reach for professional reconciliation when &ldquo;the bank feeds match&rdquo; stops being good enough.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-recon-process" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The monthly reconciliation rhythm</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">How reconciliation actually happens.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Same shape every month &mdash; not a once-a-year scramble.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n{% if loop.last %} process-step__n--done{% endif %}">{{ s.num | safe }}</div><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-recon-scope">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Honest scope</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Reconciliation vs audit, vs feeds, vs hope.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">What reconciliation is, what it isn&rsquo;t, and what stays with licensed professionals.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in scope %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ s.label | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-recon-floor" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Beyond reconciliation</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Reconciliation is the floor every other report stands on.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Once accounts reconcile each month, the rest of the practice can do its job: <a href="/accounting/financial-statements/">financial statements</a> become trustworthy, <a href="/accounting/advisory/kpi-reporting/">KPI reports</a> show what&rsquo;s really happening, <a href="/accounting/advisory/cash-flow-management/">cash flow forecasts</a> sit on real numbers, and your CPA stops doing bookkeeping at tax time. A reconciled file is the one that survives an audit, a lender&rsquo;s review, or a buyer&rsquo;s diligence without a scramble.</p>
      <p>Most TechBrot clients run reconciliation inside <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/">monthly bookkeeping</a> and then layer <a href="/accounting/advisory/?intent=advisory">advisory</a> on top &mdash; up to a <a href="/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/?intent=fractional-cfo">fractional CFO</a> seat when the work becomes continuous. As automation handles the routine, reliable reconciliation is the operational discipline that earns the right to do everything else. <a href="/accounting/advisory/?intent=advisory">Explore advisory <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal" id="acct-recon-review">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Page review &amp; standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot performs account reconciliation. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for accuracy on reconciliation methodology, source-document standards, and the boundary with licensed CPA engagements. Where our approach or scope changes, this page is updated. Reconciliation is delivered inside <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/">monthly bookkeeping</a> on a published close calendar and coordinated with your CPA for filing and any formal engagement.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:14px;">Page last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="acct-recon-related" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Related</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
